==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scantle
<hw>Scan"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Dim. of
<ets>scant</ets>, v.]</ety> <def>To be deficient; to fail.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scantle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Scantle
<hw>Scan"tle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF.
<ets>escanteler</ets>, <ets>eschanteler</ets>, to break into contles;
pref. <ets>es-</ets> (L. <ets>ex</ets>) + <ets>cantel</ets>,
<ets>chantel</ets>, corner, side, piece. Confused with E.
<ets>scant</ets>. See <er>Cantle</er>.]</ety> <def>To scant; to be
niggard of; to divide into small pieces; to cut short or down.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>All their pay⟦br⟧
Must your discretion <qex>scantle</qex>; keep it back.</q> <rj><qau>J.
Webster.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scantlet</ent>⟦br⟧
